description: MADELON is an artificial dataset created for the NIPS 2003 feature selection challenge. Data points are grouped in 32 clusters placed on the vertices of a five-dimensional hypercube and randomly labeled +1 or -1. The dataset contains 5 informative features, 15 redundant features (linear combinations of the informative features), and 480 distractor features with no predictive power. The order of features and patterns were randomized.
creator: Isabelle Guyon

feature_descriptions.informative: 5 features that constitute the five dimensions of the hypercube vertices
feature_descriptions.redundant: 15 features that are linear combinations of the 5 informative features
feature_descriptions.noise: 480 distractor features (probes) with no predictive power, following N(0,1) distribution

use_case: Feature selection challenge to test algorithms' ability to identify relevant features among many irrelevant ones in a highly non-linear, multivariate problem
ethical_considerations: As an artificial dataset, there are no direct ethical concerns. It serves as a benchmark for feature selection algorithms.
